rol during the luteal phase?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Corpus luteum formation requires follicle stimulating hormone","Corpus luteum formation requires luteinizing hormon","Corpus luteum formation requires growth hormone","Secondary oocyte formation requires follicle stimulating hormone","Secondary oocyte formation requires luteinizing hormone"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAfter ovulation, remaining follicular cells develop into \u003Cstrong\u003Ecorpus luteum\u003C/strong\u003E in the presence of \u003Cstrong\u003Eluteinizing hormone\u003C/strong\u003E. This is a critical process that occurs during the luteal phase of the menstrual cycle. While \u003Cstrong\u003Egrowth hormone\u003C/strong\u003E has some effects on ovarian function, it is not responsible for corpus luteum formation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esecondary oocyte\u003C/strong\u003E actually forms earlier during follicular development, not during the luteal phase. While \u003Cstrong\u003Efollicle stimulating hormone\u003C/strong\u003E is important for early follicular development, it is not the primary hormone responsible for corpus luteum formation and maintenance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe corpus luteum is an important structure that makes progesterone to support pregnancy and regulate the menstrual cycle.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The corpus luteum forms from the ruptured follicle during the luteal phase of the menstrual cycle","Luteinizing hormone (LH) is the hormone that stimulates corpus luteum formation"],"references":["Duncan WC. The inadequate corpus luteum. Reprod Fertil. 2021 Feb 26;2(1):C1-C7. doi: 10.1530/RAF-20-0044. PMID: 35128435; PMCID: PMC8812462.","Evans, T. J., \u0026 Ganjam, V. K. (2017). Reproductive anatomy and physiology. In Reproductive and Developmental Toxicology (pp. 7-37). Academic Press","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford University Press, USA"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56651"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15687"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56651","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56651"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-17T19:40:18+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-17T19:41:02+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8378"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71177"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"